<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Zhiyi Zhang looks great in this movie. Andy Lau (one of my favorite actors/singers) as usual does a great job. Not sure who the heck the 3rd main character is as my Mandarin sucks. Watching this on DVD with English subs. Bought it for 20 bucks plus shipping. Better than paying 9 bucks at a movie theater which doesn't include the hassle of driving, parking, and the WAY overpriced food. 
<br />

<br />
Initial impression after 30 min. Very nice cinematography. Nicely scripted fights without being too overdone like they were in Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon. Btw, the term "crouching tiger, hidden dragon" refers to the dangers that's hidden all over when one enters the world. Sorta like a tiger in the dense canopy crouching and waiting to snare you.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
