<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="88391"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#2:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Hikaru</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=88391#88391"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Sat Dec 04, 2004 4:07 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Just finished watching this. The only bad part is that I don't understand Mandarin too well so I had to rely on the subtitles. The DVD had a choice of traditional or simplified Chinese and English. The English subs were actually pretty good but there were some lines that I would have definitely changed to be more true to the original dialogue. It's directed by the same guy who did Hero with Jet Li. 
<br />

<br />
The conclusive fight was AMAZING. Very well done final fight. Again cinematography was great. There were a lot of good looking scenery with lots of nice contrasting colors. 
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I found out who the male co-star was, he's actually Japanese which would explain why I don't recognize him. Heh, I didn't look at the dvd cover, I just popped the dvd in. 
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://us.yesasia.com/en/PrdDept.aspx/pid-1003540259/did-0/code-c/section-videos/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Yes Asia sells it for $13.99 + $2.00 shipping.</a> I paid a tad more for it but only by $2.00 cause it wasn't on sale at the time. Excellent movie. If you liked Hero, Crouching Tiger, and Iron Monkey then this movie would please you. 
<br />

<br />
I should also mention the DVD is region 3 (east asia) but most computer DVD software should play it just fine. If not there are a few tools you can find online to use and disable the region checking. Or at the least to reset the region of your dvd player at will.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
