<span class="name"><a name="89369"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#3:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>greif_quellious</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=89369#89369"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Dec 13, 2004 4:12 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I saw the show in a theatre in Malaysia, with an all chinese speaking crowd.
<br />

<br />
I didn't like it and I think neither did the majority of the audience that spoke the language (and I would think would be the main demographic the film-maker is making the movie for).
<br />

<br />
I think the movie's rep (in the West) is horribly overblown and I personally feel that it pretentious and illogical. It also commits the worst cinematic sin in my eyes - its gets pretty boring in the middle part IMHO. Really, I think this movie was banged out to take advantage of the good buzz generated by the previous film the director did - "Hero" (whom i thought was just kinda okay - not great, just ok).
<br />

<br />
The movie really needed a strong editor to prune out the meandering stuff in the middle. 
<br />

<br />
MINOR SPOILER:
<br />
The ending sequence of the movie...
<br />
Sheesh, I think it really killed the "impression" of the film for me. The word SILLY comes to mind. Another word is ENDLESS. The audience i was with giggled throughout the ending sequence and i feel for them too. The audience (and I) was giggling not because the movie was intentionally funny but at ..... I would put it charitably .... artistic flair taken a wee bit too far (and for too long). Somebody, anybody .... actor, producer, editor, cameraman... should have said to the director, "You know, thats really gonna look stupid on screen."*
<br />

<br />
Weak movie, some nice fight sequences, lax editing and overly indulgent  "pretentious" directing (thats evident in the last quarter of the movie). Nowhere near as good IMO as CTHD or even Hero (which itself was just a personal "ok").
<br />

<br />
* I may ROT13 post what it was in the ending that bothered me, the audience and the majority of the people i polled; if anyone asks.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
